1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,600
The moment in the garden, the
idea of allowing your own crucifixion.

2
00:00:12,040 --> 00:00:14,760
But you're not a Christian,
so what do you believe?

3
00:00:15,960 --> 00:00:18,721
I believe that people shouldn't
talk about this type of shit at work.

4
00:00:18,840 --> 00:00:20,120
Hold on, hold on.

5
00:00:22,500 --> 00:00:26,280
Three months we've been
together, I get nothing from you.

6
00:00:26,281 --> 00:00:31,880
And today, what we're into
now, do me a courtesy, okay?

7
00:00:31,900 --> 00:00:33,720
I'm not trying to convert you.

8
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:36,260
Look, I'd consider
myself a realist, all right?

9
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:39,200
But in philosophical terms,
I'm what's called a pessimist.

10
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,620
Um, okay, what's that mean?

11
00:00:42,580 --> 00:00:44,000
It means I'm bad at parties.

12
00:00:46,020 --> 00:00:49,400
Let me tell you, you ain't
great outside of parties either.

13
00:00:56,280 --> 00:01:00,840
I think human consciousness
is a tragic misstep in evolution.

14
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:03,420
We became too self-aware.

15
00:01:04,320 --> 00:01:07,820
Nature created an aspect
of nature separate from itself.

16
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,540
We are creatures that
should not exist by natural law.

17
00:01:12,040 --> 00:01:14,920
Hmm, that sounds god-fucking-awful, Rush.

18
00:01:15,121 --> 00:01:19,580
We are things that labor under
the illusion of having a self.

19
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:23,500
This accretion of sensory
experience and feeling.

20
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:28,180
Programmed with total assurance
that we are each somebody.

21
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:31,720
When in fact, everybody's nobody.

22
00:01:31,980 --> 00:01:34,500
I wouldn't go around
spouting that shit out with you.

23
00:01:34,600 --> 00:01:37,200
People around here don't think that way.

24
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:38,340
I don't think that way.

25
00:01:38,341 --> 00:01:42,540
I think the honorable thing for our
species to do is deny our programming.

26
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:45,840
Stop reproducing.

27
00:01:46,620 --> 00:01:48,900
Walk hand in hand into extinction.

28
00:01:49,620 --> 00:01:53,520
One last midnight, brothers and
sisters opting out of a raw deal.

29
00:01:57,120 --> 00:02:00,440
So, what's the point of getting
out of bed in the morning?

30
00:02:00,620 --> 00:02:02,300
I tell myself I bear witness.

31
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:06,280
The real answer is that it's
obviously my programming.

32
00:02:07,581 --> 00:02:10,720
And I lack the constitution for suicide.

33
00:02:10,980 --> 00:02:14,720
My luck, I picked today to get to know you.

34
00:02:14,980 --> 00:02:17,800
Three months, I don't hear a
word from you and...

35
00:02:17,824 --> 00:02:18,524
You asked.

36
00:02:18,600 --> 00:02:18,780
Yeah.

37
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:21,760
And now I'm begging
you to shut the fuck up.

38
00:02:30,420 --> 00:02:32,540
I've got a bad taste in my mouth out here.

39
00:02:34,060 --> 00:02:35,060
Aluminum.

40
00:02:35,420 --> 00:02:35,900
Ash.

41
00:02:37,980 --> 00:02:40,540
I can smell the psychosphere.

42
00:02:40,620 --> 00:02:41,640
I got an idea.

43
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:46,660
Let's make the car a place of
silent reflection from now on.

44
00:02:47,620 --> 00:02:48,620
Okay?

45
00:02:58,721 --> 00:02:59,961
What should I bring for dinner?

46
00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:06,420
A bottle of wine would be nice, I guess.

47
00:03:10,021 --> 00:03:11,540
I don't drink.

48
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:14,300
Oh, no, of course not, Russ.

49
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:18,580
Listen, when you're at my house,
I want you to chill the fuck out.

50
00:03:18,660 --> 00:03:21,500
Don't even mention any of
that bullshit you just said to me.

51
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,640
Of course not, Marty.

52
00:03:23,160 --> 00:03:24,740
I'm not some kind of maniac, right?

53
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:27,000
Well, for fuck's sake.

